        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> December 1861</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Revd &amp; dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I read with much plea„<lb/>„sure your issue of Povbr<add>?</add> a
                p, and as I am interested in<lb/>
                <persName>P's</persName> letter I beg to thank you for its publication. I
                regret<lb/> to say that our <persName>Revd Mr. M</persName> has not escaped the fate
                of<lb/> most good men and his good intentions and honest perseverance<lb/> are
                doubted by a <sic>handfull</sic> of his congregation, thanks to<lb/> God it is the
                worst judging portion, still they may influence<lb/> enemies against him in
                countries where they are not known.<lb/> Therefore as eulogions<add>?</add> have
                appeared in your paper in his favor<lb/> and his <sic>entagonist</sic> may select
                the same field to attack him<lb/> I address you these few lines, as it were to put
                you on your<lb/> guard; I am aware that the principle under which you<lb/> conduct
                your valuable &amp; much esteemed Occident, is to allow<lb/> free discussions, but I
                am certain when those discussions aim to<lb/> destroy the reputation of a faithful
                servant of <placeName>Israel's</placeName> God you<lb/> will know with what contempt
                to treat them, and not lend<lb/> your periodical to such purposes. I inform you this
                much<lb/> that you may know in case you are addressed, otherwise please<lb/> not to
                mention anything to the public, as I wish not to be the<lb/> means of exposing any
                little difficulties which may exist among<lb/> us. <persName>Mr Myers</persName>
                friends are the most respectable members of<lb/> his congregation, besides I am
                happy to say he enjoys the esteem<lb/> of the whole community,
                    <persName>N's</persName> letter therefore expressed the views</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of a respectable majority.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">MDAsorio</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
